														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4237568">
									

<p>I like the idea of an article that examines a monster in detail, but this is falling short for me. By far the most important ability 4975 has as a predator is killing people and eating them without actually leaving its cell, which this article lazily sidesteps with SRAs. Failing to truly address that ability undermines the rest of this, because the details of how that long distance attack works seem way more important than the relatively mundane facts about persistence hunting (which mostly describe adaptations that would be made totally obsolete by its telekinesis anyway).</p>

							</div>

								
					
