					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ch00bakka" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1238719); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1238719&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224943" alt="ch00bakka" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1238719)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ch00bakka" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1238719); return false;" >ch00bakka</a></span> <span class="odate time_1556912522 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 May 2019 19:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4237725">
									

<p>i actually have the same problem with telekill as fieldstone does with SRAs (not that SRAs would be any better) - it seems like a lazy handwave, and I'm not really sure why blocking telepathy would necessarily do anything. (also, the Foundation would call it SCP-148, rather than telekill.)</p>

