															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/k-solari" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4429802); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4429802&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224943" alt="K_Solari" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4429802)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/k-solari" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4429802); return false;" >K_Solari</a></span> <span class="odate time_1556913608 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 May 2019 20:00</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4237734">
									

<p>Well, the idea is that the attacks performed by 4975 are telekinetic in nature, and given that telekill's literature has been expanded to show how it halts/weakens telekinesis, it made sense to use it. And to be fair, telekill is about the only way I could have advocated containing it without saying &quot;just let it keep attacking people&quot;, which would have serious ethical issues. I also believe it introduces some risk because telekill does have the fact that it releases the energy after a time, meaning that if these procedures are wrong in the long run or they don't completely discharge as expected, then there would still be risks involved. Either way, I tried to do my research, and I believe it would be rather silly of the foundation to not do anything, so I chose the path that keeps in some literary risks and chooses a realistic option.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>“Being in a minority, even in a minority of one, did not make you mad. There was truth and there was untruth, and if you clung to the truth even against the whole world, you were not mad.”<br />
― George Orwell, 1984</p>

				</div>
					
					
